helpdesk-ticket.subject: Jenzabar on OS X
helpdesk-ticket.description: Mark Anderson is going outside of the country. He is wondering if he can use a version of Jenzabar on his Mac, instead of having to take his MSOE laptop with him on the trip. I couldn't find anything online about a mac version. Perhaps he could set up a windows partition. He is planning on coming in to the desk on the 24th to talk it over.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Mark Anderson is going outside of the country. He is wondering if he can use a version of Jenzabar on his Mac, instead of having to take his MSOE laptop with him on the trip. I couldn't find anything online about a mac version. Perhaps he could set up a windows partition. He is planning on coming in to the desk on the 24th to talk it over.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Mark,
Jenzabar EX is not available for Mac OS. It is strictly a Windows-based product.
Also, the Jenzabar client can not be installed on any non-university owned machine.
If you would like to discuss options for access while on your trip, please let me know when you'll have some time today.
Thanks, Jen Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/1207

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Matlab uninstallation and reinstallation
helpdesk-ticket.description: Andrew Samson was having issues with matlab and needed it uninstalled and reinstalled. During the process I noticed that the DNS servers were set to rogue servers that many computer with viruses have them set to. I changed the DNS servers back to default and let malwarebytes run in the background during the installation. After reinstallation and fixing the DNS servers matlab worked properly.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Andrew Samson was having issues with matlab and needed it uninstalled and reinstalled. During the process I noticed that the DNS servers were set to rogue servers that many computer with viruses have them set to. helpdesk-ticket.subject: HP Zbook Crashing after 1 hour
helpdesk-ticket.description: Currently I am studying internationally so I can only be contacted through my MSOE email at the moment. I am having quite a bit of trouble with my new HP Zbook that I just recieved at the beginning of my Junior year. It has done this probably about 10 times already, I log in perfectly the computer runs just fine and after about 1 hour it crashes and the computer freezes. All i have installed so far is avast antivirus so I can't image that I could have gotten a virus. I have only ran the computer about 10 times as well. Sometimes after crashing it will unfreeze after about 10 minutes or so but usually i have to turn off the computer in order for it to work again. Do you have any suggestions on any resets or quick fixes I could try? Thanks, Jonah Mrozinsky

This issue is actually caused by having Avast Antivirus installed. Already installed on the computers is Trend Micro OfficeScan. This is the MSOE provided antivirus. When you have 2 antiviruses on the computer they will often fight with each other and cause odd issues. This is likely the case.
I recommend that you uninstall Avast. This should fix the issue.
Thanks, Kevin MSOE IT helpdesk@msoe.edu (414)-277-7288

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jonah Mrozinsky,
The issue that your having with the laptop is most likely connected to having both the trend micro office scan client and avast antivirus installed at the same time. These programs can interfere with each other and cause the whole computer to run slowly. Uninstalling Avast should fix your issue. If you continue to have issue then please reply to this ticket.
Thanks, MSOE Information Technology Cameron Wilson 414-277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Trouble Submitting zip file on Blackboard
helpdesk-ticket.description: Ivan had tried to submit his web design assignment on Blackboard as a zip file but his professor said when he tried to open it he would get an error. It turned out he had submitted a zipped copy of the shortcut file on his desktop. Placed project and necessary files in a folder, zipped, and submitted on Blackboard. We tested downloading and opening the file. If not extracted to a local place on the computer, the assignment (which is a web design) wouldn't find the pictures and linked documents. Showed how and where to extract file so assignment would work.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Ivan had tried to submit his web design assignment on Blackboard as a zip file but his professor said when he tried to open it he would get an error. It turned out he had submitted a zipped copy of the shortcut file on his desktop. Placed project and necessary files in a folder, zipped, and submitted on Blackboard.
We tested downloading and opening the file. If not extracted to a local place on the computer, the assignment (which is a web design) wouldn't find the pictures and linked documents. Showed how and where to extract file so assignment would work.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Internet issues in dormitories
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hi,
My name is Jordan Bender. I was wondering if there was any way to resolve the issue of XBOX Ones not being able to play online in the dormitory buildings. From my research I have found that the most likely issue is port 84 being closed. XBOX One is the first system to require that port to be open in order to have a non-strict NAT type. Please let me know at your earliest convenience what there is to resolve the issue.
Regards, Jordan Bender
Sent using OWA for iPhone
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:

From my research I have found that the most likely issue is port 84 being closed. XBOX One is the first system to require that port to be open in order to have a non-strict NAT type. Please let me know at your earliest convenience what there is to resolve the issue.

Regards,
Jordan Bender

Sent using OWA for iPhone

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jordan Bender,
I'm sorry to inform you that there is current no solution to the issue that students are having with the xbox one's NAT requirements. The issue revolves around the fact that the xbox uses peer to peer connection to run its game server. These connections are very similar to those that are used in bit torrent traffic to the point at which it is impossible to filter them out. We block that kind of traffic on our network for security reasons. We currently do not have any recommended solutions to this issue. Sorry for the inconvenience. If you have any questions please reply to this ticket.
Thanks, MSOE Information Technology Cameron Wilson 414-277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu

helpdesk-ticket.subject: msoe.edu hub still lists me as a "prospective student"
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
In my attempt to open an IT ticket regarding my user type being listed as a "prospective student" when logged into the msoe.edu main page, I also found I was unable to log in to the IT support portal to open a formal service request ticket. Could you please help me correct these two items?
Item 1 - When logged into msoe.edu I'm listed as a "prospective student". Item 2 - IT support portal would not accept my login credentials.
Thanks for your help!
Regards, Chris Brook
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hello,
 
In my attempt to open an IT ticket regarding my user type being listed as a “prospective student” when logged into the msoe.edu main page, I also found I was unable to log in to the IT support portal to open a formal service request ticket. Could you please help me correct these two items?
 
Item 1 – When logged into msoe.edu I’m listed as a “prospective student”.
Item 2 – IT support portal would not accept my login credentials.
 
Thanks for your help!
 
Regards,
Chris Brook

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Chris, In regards to issue #1. The reason that you may still be showing a perspective student status on the Hub may be due to a issue with switching your personal login to the hub over to a msoe login. Do you still log into the HUB issues and personal email. If so them follow this link and use our hub switcher tool to move over to a msoe login (https://webprod.msoe.edu/switcher_app/). Select the switch form a personal login option. If you are still having issues, or have already completed this step in the past and currently use a @msoe.edu email to log into the hub, let us know and we can help you further on this subject.
In regards to issue #2. The Reason that you may have been having issues logging into our IT support portal is that you may need to reset the password. This can be achieved through the forgot password option that is located on the login page. This option will allow you to reset the password, which will be sent to you through your MSOE email. If you having any issue feel free to reply to this ticket or to give us a call at 414-277-7288.
I hope this helps solve your issues
Thanks, MSOE Information Technology Cameron Wilson 414-277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu

helpdesk-ticket.description: Hi, I regularly use the outlook app on the desktop and have been unable to open it since I updated my email password.

helpdesk-note.body:
Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/1277 Hi, I regularly use the outlook app on the desktop and have been unable to open it since I updated my email password.
Hi Jessica Bade,
This is a relatively common issue, it has to do with the way Outlook stores saved passwords. To fix it, open up the start menu and type in "credential manager". The icon should be a picture of a safe. Once inside the credential manager, there should be three categories, Windows Credentials, Certificate Based Credentials, and Generic Credentials. Under Generic Credentials there should be an entry that says "MS.Outlook.15:badejl@msoe.edu". Click on it, and select the option to remove from vault. Do this for all MS.Outlook credentials. Once this is completed, close Outlook if you already have it open and reopen it. A login box should open up, log in with your new password and your emails should load as normal.
Nathan Stachowiak
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/1277
Hi, I regularly use the outlook app on the desktop and have been unable to open it since I updated my email password.


Hi Jessica Bade,

This is a relatively common issue, it has to do with the way Outlook stores saved passwords. To fix it, open up the start menu and type in "credential manager". The icon should be a picture of a safe. Once inside the credential manager, there should be three categories, Windows Credentials, Certificate Based Credentials, and Generic Credentials. Under Generic Credentials there should be an entry that says "MS.Outlook.15:badejl@msoe.edu". Click on it, and select the option to remove from vault. Do this for all MS.Outlook credentials. Once this is completed, close Outlook if you already have it open and reopen it. A login box should open up, log in with your new password and your emails should load as normal.

Nathan Stachowiak

helpdesk-ticket.subject: CC 03 VGA cable
helpdesk-ticket.description:
The projector's VGA cable in CC 03 is bent and will not attach to a laptop any more. It needs to be replaced. I used another VGA cable to get through a presentation this morning, but the cable should be replaced before Dr. Hornick needs it for his classes.
I wonder if it would make sense to use some sort of tie to attach the free end of the cable to the instructor's podium that's in the room. I think the connector is getting bent when people accidentally roll chairs over it. If the cable is reasonably long, it shouldn't be a serious problem if the podium is tethered to the screen area. If someone needs to present while sitting at a table (as opposed to standing at the podium), they should be able to connect to the TV monitor in the room instead.
Rob

helpdesk-note.body: sending to AV
helpdesk-note.body-html: sending to AV

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Rob, I've re-bent the VGA connection that was damaged, and plugged it to the wall (so that the undamaged one is now on the podium). I've checked that the screen still displays correctly, so I think we can get a little more life out of the current cable. In addition, I've added a "hook" to the side of the podium to hang the cable. I don't want to attach it permamently to any specific table or podium, as I know not everyone uses the podium. But hopefully we can encourage people to at least try to keep it off of the floor(?) helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jill Tronca, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/1335
Jill Tronca called the helpdesk about trying to set up her father's email account to work on a personal desktop with Outlook 2007 installed. I attempted to help her set up a new outlook account, but upon doing some research I realized that I was making a mistake during the account set up. I was not specifying the type of security being used. I attached the directions on setting up the email account to this ticket, and will send a message directly to Jill about this issue.
Ticket attachments : 1. Hosted_Exchange_IMAP_POP_Email_Settings.pdf
Jill,
I realized that when we were trying to set up the tronca@msoe.edu email account in Outlook that we were not setting up the security type correctly. This was preventing us from actually connecting. Please follow the instructions in the attached document. For your convenience I will also paste that part of the instructions here.
Incoming Server – outlook.office365.com
Incoming Port – 993 (IMAP) or 995 (POP)
Security – SSL/TLS
Outgoing Server – outlook.office365.com (POP) or smtp.office365.com (IMAP) or m.outlook.com (Gmail)
Outgoing Port – 587
Security – STARTTLS Please let us know if these settings and instructions do not solve your problem. Feel free to give us a call if you need help with this further. Have a great day!
Helpdesk Technician Justin

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Emily Vogel,
We have set up the printers to open a ticket if they are low on paper, jammed, low on toner (10%), or if there is an error in the print job queue. In addition, we have asked Tier 1 helpdesk to make a paper run twice a week to areas near printers and verify paper stock. Let us know if you continue to run into issues. We're still ironing out the details of the new printer process.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Dr. Walter Schilling,
Things to consider:
There is an outbound limit set by Office 365 on the number of sent emails per day. 10,000 per day, or a maximum of 500 addresses per email. We do not control this limit, but I doubt you are hitting it
If you are copying/BBCing yourself on these emails, they will create a send loop and not leave your outbox
The outbox can get corrupted in some cases. If these emails sent in webmail but not Outlook, it could be a corrupted outbox. I can only find a repair solution online for Outlook Express, but I believe there is an Office took for repairing installs. Tier 2 may have better knowledge of such a tool.
Hopefully one of the first two things will correct your issue and you won't need to reinstall Outlook.

Hello!
I have been having problems printing on campus today.
This is the first time I have tried printing this year with the new printers. Is there something I have to change on my computer?
Zak Wroblewski
Hi Zak,
To connect to the new printer system, open the start menu and type in "run". Inside the box, type "\\printers" and hit enter, this should pop up with a window with multiple printer icons. Select the one that says "Follow You Printing", right click on it and select "connect..".
Nathan Stachowiak
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/1365
Hello!
 
I have been having problems printing on campus today.
This is the first time I have tried printing this year with the new printers. Is there something I have to change on my computer?
 
Zak Wroblewski



Hi Zak,

To connect to the new printer system, open the start menu and type in "run". Inside the box, type "\\printers" and hit enter, this should pop up with a window with multiple printer icons. Select the one that says "Follow You Printing", right click on it and select "connect..". 

Nathan Stachowiak

Hi Mark,
Emily put in a ticket for this today and I explained the situation to her. She said per her documentation you were both on 7391 at some point but that point was very possibly quite a while ago so she is going to update her documentation and handle it from her side.
You should inform students your number is 2750 as you will get that voicemail in your email. The voicemail pin is 124578. You can set it up by:
Seen as you have a shared phone these instructions have a couple more steps then normal. 1. Hit the voicemail button it looks like an envelope with 2 sideways wifi arcs coming out of it. 2. Hit the asterix key 3. Type 2750 and hit pound 4. Type the pin(124578) and hit pound 5. It will automaticly put you in your mailbox setup where you can set a greeting and a new pin.
Thanks, Tony

Hi Mark,

Emily put in a ticket for this today and I explained the situation to her. She said per her documentation you were both on 7391 at some point but that point was very possibly quite a while ago so she is going to update her documentation and handle it from her side.

You should inform students your number is 2750 as you will get that voicemail in your email. The voicemail pin is 124578. You can set it up by:

Seen as you have a shared phone these instructions have a couple more steps then normal.
1. Hit the voicemail button it looks like an envelope with 2 sideways wifi arcs coming out of it. 
2. Hit the asterix key
3. Type 2750 and hit pound
4. Type the pin(124578) and hit pound
5. It will automaticly put you in your mailbox setup where you can set a greeting and a new pin.


Thanks,
Tony

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Reading Video Card off of Sony Camera
helpdesk-ticket.description: Kathy's student could not get movie off of sony camcorder. She believed she couldn't install the right drivers. When you connect the device to the computer via usb the drivers are installed automatically. On the camcorder screen, it asks for what kind of connection you want, whether to the dvd or memory card. The right side option is the memory card. From there the files can be read by the computer.

The right side option is the memory card. From there the files can be read by the computer.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Op Computer 11/20: laptops, etc.
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I look forward to coordinating the Op Computer competition again this year. I appreciate IT's help over the years by providing both your employees for laptop checkout, etc., and finding enough laptop computers to accommodate all the high school teams which asked to register for the competition. The event will be run at its traditional time: the morning of Friday of week 11 of the fall quarter (11/20). The laptops will be checked out to the competitors at 7:30 AM and checked back in to IT personnel at 11:15 AM. The entire competition will take place on the 3rd floor of the CC.
I anticipate needing around 50 MSOE laptop computers of any vintage for this event. I checked with Peter Pfister and he said that we can easily meet this number this year. I will be in touch to refine the number as registrations come in and the competition approaches. We encourage teams to bring their own laptops (2 per team), but not all are able to. I anticipate roughly 30-40 teams (60-80 laptops), with roughly half bringing their own laptops.
I will help set up a laptop to be imaged. We'll use a simplified setup similar to what we did in 2014. The laptops (both user-provided and IT-provided) will need MSOE wireless network access. The laptops will access the competition management app that we'll set up on sapphire.msoe.edu again this year. For the IT-provided laptops, I will set up Java and C++ environments to be imaged, including recent versions of Microsoft Visual Studio, Eclipse, and BlueJ.

Hi edgem, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/1403 The local ethernet on the wall is not working. My desktop receives no local area connection. Also my roommates smart tv gets no internet as well. We have tried different cables and it is confirmed to be the wall. Please fix this soon.
I went in and tested port t-901-1 which is the port that the desktop computer was plugged into. i got a solid connection on the first try and did a speed test to verify a quality connection. see below.
http://www.speedtest.net/my-result/4712997534
if there are other issues please submit a ticket with specific issues. thanks.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: A/V Request - STEM Expo - 10/10
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
As a part of the upcoming STEM Expo at the Kern Center Fieldhouse on 10/10/15, we have need for the following A/V equipment:
* (1) TV
* (1) projector on a cart (Traffic Bowl area)
* (1) projector screen (traffic bowl area)
* (1) small sound system with 4 tabletop mics (Traffic Bowl area)
* (1) Overall field house sound system for general announcements. Wireless mic preferred, if available
I have attached the layout for the event in the fieldhouse for clarity, you can see that the area labeled "traffic bowl" is where most of the items will need to be setup. The equipment would need to be setup by 8am, and the event runs until 3pm on Saturday the 10th. Both sound systems will not need to be used at the same time, in case that's helpful information for setup.
Thank you for your help! Please let me know what additional information I can provide regarding this request.
Regards,

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Issues with Microsoft Outlook not loading images
helpdesk-ticket.description: Alexander Vetroczky was having an issue where any office related programs would not display any images. This was not fixed via repair install or reinstalling the programs. When I changed the setting for hardware acceleration to do not use per an online suggestion office programs would only display solid white. I recommended that Alexander back up his data so that the computer could have a freshly imaged hard drive. After replacing the hard drive with a freshly imaged one he was able to use office suite products as usual.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: FW: A/V NEEDS: Parents Weekend (Fri.-Sun., October 9-11)
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Forward from old AV Account
From: Seidler, Nicholas Sent: Thursday, October 01, 2015 2:39 PM To: AV; Kann, Jason; Hurlbut, Patricia Cc: Seidler, Nicholas; Donohew, Elizabeth Subject: A/V NEEDS: Parents Weekend (Fri.-Sun., October 9-11) Importance: High
A/V NEEDS for PARENTS AND FAMILY WEEKEND
Hi Pat and Jason,
There are very few A/V Needs that we have for parents and family weekend but I wanted to follow up to make sure that we have these small items covered. I have comments in HIGHLIGHT for each of the events that use sound. ONLY THE TRIVIA EVENT needs any special setup or equipment from what is already in the spaces - it is HIGHLIGHTED in GREEN.
I will be at most of these events (and for sure the trivia event on Saturday night). My cell is (414) 940-2831 if you need anything or details from me.
Just want to be sure that we have this on the schedule and that we have the sound at the trivia event.
Thank you for all your help,
-Nick
FRIDAY, OCTOBER 9
7:30 pm - 10:30 pm
Society of Model Engineers Train Presentation
Location: Cudahy Student Center - Multipurpose Room (Campus Center - 3rd Floor)
Come and learn about real and model trains at the this presentation open to all. Hosted by MSOE's model railroad club, the Society of Model Engineers.
[cid:image012.jpg@01D0F53B.FBDCEDE0]
Using MPR Projector and Sound (already in the room)
8 pm - 9:30 pm
Hypnotist Jim Wand
Location: Kern Center Arena (Kern Center - 1st Floor)
Come and see world renown hypnotist Dr. Jim Wand explain hypnotism and entrance members of the audience in the fun and hilarious show!
[http://tickets.grandfallscasinoresort.com/uplimage/JimWand.jpg]
Jim Wand Brings Sound but in case have Kern Sound System and Mic with Stand in reserve for use.
SATURDAY, OCTOBER 10
10 am - Noon
Parents and Family Brunch
Location: Grohmann Museum - Roof Top Garden (4th Floor) [Rain Site: Grohman Museum Auditorium - 1st Floor]
Join on top of the Grohmann Museum, home of the world famous Man-At-Work art collection, for a relaxing brunch with a wonderful view of the city!
[http://webprod.msoe.edu/who-we-are/wp-content/uploads/sites/25/2013/03/img-grohmann-rooftop-photos-330x186.jpg]
Music in Grohmann, already in place, controlled by Grohammn we believe (let us know if not the case).
10 am - 3 pm
STEM Expo Event
Location: Kern Center Field House (2nd Floor)
Learn about the world of Science, Technology, Engineering, and Mathematics (STEM) through hands-on exploration stations and demonstrations.
http://www.ascewise.org/stem-expo/
[STEM Expo 2014]
Special sound would have been separately coordinated by STEM Department.
8 pm - 9:30 pm
Team Trivia Event
Location: Cudahy Student Center (Campus Center - 3rd Floor)
Form a team with your family, friends, or roommates and see if you can win some of the many cash prizes we have for the event. Questions can be about any topic, so working together will help you get to the top! Teams can be any size, but using smartphones or the internet is not allowed. Hosted by the Student Union Board.
[cid:image037.jpg@01D0F53B.FBDCEDE0][cid:image038.jpg@01D0F53B.FBDCEDE0]
*** NEED MIXING BOARD, 2 MICS, AND PA SPEAKERS TO COVER THE ROOM, and a MINI CORD ATTACHMENT between a laptop and the mixing board. [Setup is on the middle raised area (game room) between sky dining raised area and TV raised area (a speaker facing each direction 2 Speakers have been fine in the past); A mini-connector to play sound from a laptop into the mixing board is needed for playing music. 2 microphones are needed to read the trivia questions and rules ).
SUNDAY, OCTOBER 11
10 am - Noon
Continental Breakfast Family Farewell
Location: Grohmann Tower Apartments (4th Floor)
Grab a little coffee or continental breakfast before you say farewell at MSOE's new Grohmann Tower apartment building!
[cid:image040.jpg@01D0F53B.FBDCEDE0]
Using existing screen/projector In Grohmann Tower.

There are very few A/V Needs that we have for parents and family weekend but I wanted to follow up to make sure that we have these small items covered.  I have comments in HIGHLIGHT for each of the events that use sound.  ONLY THE TRIVIA EVENT needs any special setup or equipment from what is already in the spaces – it is HIGHLIGHTED in GREEN.
 
I will be at most of these events (and for sure the trivia event on Saturday night).  My cell is (414) 940-2831 if you need anything or details from me.
 
Just want to be sure that we have this on the schedule and that we have the sound at the trivia event.
 
Thank you for all your help,
 
-Nick
 
 
 
 
FRIDAY, OCTOBER 9
  
7:30 pm – 10:30 pm
Society of Model Engineers Train Presentation
Location: Cudahy Student Center – Multipurpose Room (Campus Center - 3rd Floor)
Come and learn about real and model trains at the this presentation open to all.  Hosted by MSOE’s model railroad club, the Society of Model Engineers.
Using MPR Projector and Sound (already in the room)
 
8 pm – 9:30 pm
Hypnotist Jim Wand
Location: Kern Center Arena (Kern Center - 1st Floor)
Come and see world renown hypnotist Dr. Jim Wand explain hypnotism and entrance members of the audience in the fun and hilarious show!
Jim Wand Brings Sound but in case have Kern Sound System and Mic with Stand in reserve for use.
 
 
SATURDAY, OCTOBER 10
                                                                                               
10 am – Noon
Parents and Family Brunch
Location: Grohmann Museum – Roof Top Garden (4th Floor) [Rain Site: Grohman Museum Auditorium – 1st Floor]
Join on top of the Grohmann Museum, home of the world famous Man-At-Work art collection, for a relaxing brunch with a wonderful view of the city!
Music in Grohmann, already in place, controlled by Grohammn we believe (let us know if not the case).
 
10 am – 3 pm
STEM Expo Event
Location: Kern Center Field House (2nd Floor)
Learn about the world of Science, Technology, Engineering, and Mathematics (STEM) through hands-on exploration stations and demonstrations.
http://www.ascewise.org/stem-expo/
Special sound would have been separately coordinated by STEM Department.
 
8 pm – 9:30 pm
Team Trivia Event
Location: Cudahy Student Center (Campus Center - 3rd Floor)
Form a team with your family, friends, or roommates and see if you can win some of the many cash prizes we have for the event.  Questions can be about any topic, so working together will help you get to the top!  Teams can be any size, but using smartphones or the internet is not allowed.  Hosted by the Student Union Board.
 
*** NEED MIXING BOARD, 2 MICS, AND PA SPEAKERS TO COVER THE ROOM, and a MINI CORD ATTACHMENT between a laptop and the mixing board.  [Setup is on the middle raised area (game room) between sky dining raised area and TV raised area (a speaker facing each direction 2 Speakers have been fine in the past); A mini-connector to play sound from a laptop into the mixing board is needed for playing music.  2 microphones are needed to read the trivia questions and rules ).    
 
 
 
SUNDAY, OCTOBER 11
 
10 am – Noon
Continental Breakfast Family Farewell
Location: Grohmann Tower Apartments (4th Floor)
Grab a little coffee or continental breakfast before you say farewell at MSOE’s new Grohmann Tower apartment building!
 
Using existing screen/projector In Grohmann Tower.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Excel Documents Asking for Authentication when opening with IE.
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Dear Anne Deisinger,
I'm making this ticket just to document what we talked about on the phone, in case any similar problems arise, and maybe to solve the issue related to IE.
Anne Deisinger called about having issues in Blackboard after a recent password change. When trying to access files from BB, especially Excel type files, IE would require a username and password. Anne would type her new password, and it would just immediately ask for a username/password again. I think this is due to IE having saved her previous password, which would fail when trying to autocomplete the sign-in. We went to Settings > Internet Options > Content > AutoComplete Settings > and deselected Usernames and Passwords on Forms, then clicked Okay.
I believe that this just prevents IE from saving passwords in the future. In order to solve the current problem, we need to go back to Settings > Internet Options > Content > AutoComplete Settings > and click on "Delete Autocomplete HIstory" near the bottom of that menu. I believe this will solve the issue on Internet Explorer.
Anyways, we logged into BB in Google Chrome and it worked fine. So that was a work-around. I just wanted to document the possible solution for IE as well.
Have a great day!
- Technician Justin

helpdesk-note.body:
Hello,
I need your MAC address in order to get you a standalone Matlab license.
If you are using Windows
Option 1: Volume Serial Number (Standalone licenses only) To obtain the Volume Serial Number, open a Command Prompt window, and run the command: vol c: Use the serial number listed (ex. 1234-1234).
Option 2: MAC Address (Physical Address, Standalone or Network licenses) To obtain the MAC Address, open a Command Prompt window, and run the command: getmac Use the first Physical Address listed (ex. 00-11-22-aa-bb-cc).
If you are using a MAC For a Mac OS X machine, the host ID is the MAC Address of the built in Ethernet device (en0). To obtain this value, use Terminal in /Applications/Utilities and run the command: netstat -I en0 The host ID is listed in the first row of the output, under the "Address" column.
